The paper discusses the challenges of using deep learning in safety-critical applications and proposes a solution for requirements traceability in neural network development. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the software engineering (cs.SE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The focus on safety-critical applications also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential security implications of deep learning, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
